This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Neural Machine Translation (NMT) and Cross-lingual Information Retrieval (CLIR) tasks. It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it focuses on improving the translation process for search queries. Additionally, the paper uses multi-task learning, which is a popular technique in the fields of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper mentions regularization, which is a common concept in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
